  "body": "Discovered this during the Hack Money hackathon.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1646497/80554852-518ae680-8983-11ea-9870-0116f0c71110.png)\r\n\r\nbuilder uses mocha@5.2.0 which uses mkdirp@0.5.1 which uses minimist@0.0.8. When I uploaded my newly buidler'd repo to GitHub, I received this complaint about a critical security vulnerability.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1646497/80554951-9e6ebd00-8983-11ea-8b4e-e62969514683.png)\r\n\r\nDetails here: https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-vh95-rmgr-6w4m\r\n\r\nPerhaps this could be fixed by updating to mocha@7.1.2, which updates mkdirp to v.0.5.5?\r\n\r\nLooks like mkdirp is getting the boot from mocha@8.0.0 (they discuss the vulnerability here): https://github.com/mochajs/mocha/issues/4199",
